                        <h2>Delivery and shipping policy</h2>
                        <p>We at E-Pharmacy want to give you the best pharmacy experience, including ensuring you receive your packages safe, sound and in a timely fashion. E-Pharmacy ships medications in secure packaging to everywhere in British Columbia, Alberta, Yukon, and Northwest Territories. We have an agreement with Canada Post as our primary shipping partner.</p>
                        <p>Once you’ve signed up with E-Pharmacy and we have your prescription on file, you should receive your first delivery in 5-7 business days. Check your email or app notification for updates on your first delivery. You will be provided a tracking number to monitor your package’s location and expected delivery date. We will ship your medication in discreet packaging to protect your privacy and use tamper evident seals for security. If you experience delays, please call us right away. If your package arrives damaged or with broken seals, let us know the tracking number provided with your package and we will replace it right away.</p>
                        <p>If you do not receive your medication and your package cannot be located using the tracking number provided, contact our office and we will re-ship the medication to you free of charge.</p>
                        <p>E-Pharmacy provides free delivery for all regular shipments. If you need any emergency medication, we can ship it to you overnight, however please be aware an additional overnight charge may be applied.</p>
                        <p>Use the Site to schedule your delivery for whatever location is most convenient for you, including at home or work. Not all employers allow you to receive personal packages at work. If your employer does not allow you to receive personal packages at work, please update your shipping address on your Account or call us to update your Account information.</p>
                        <p>Canada Post, one of our shipping partners, offers Flex Delivery™ – a unique service that allows you to have packages delivered to any post office, free of charge. To learn more or sign up for this service, visit <a href="canadapost.ca/flex">canadapost.ca/flex delivery</a>.</p>
                        <p>You get to decide whether you want your package to require a signature. If you do not want this security feature, your package will be left in your mailbox or a safe drop location on your premises.</p>
                        <p>If your package requires a signature, but no one is available, a Delivery Notice Card will be left in the mailbox indicating the closest Canada Post location to pick up your parcel.</p>
                        <p>To pick up your medication package from the post office, you must bring</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>A government-issued photo ID</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>If someone else is picking up your medication package on your behalf, they must bring one of the following:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>A government-issued photo ID showing they live at the same address as you, or</li>
                            <li>The delivery notice card signed by you showing you give them permission to pick up your package, or</li>
                            <li>A legal document that demonstrates the person has authority to act on your behalf, such as power of attorney, appointment as trustee or a letter of authorization.</li>
                        </ul>                        
                        <p>Your package will be held at the post office for a maximum of 15 days, after which it will be returned to us. Please let us know if you are unable to pick up your package within the window of time indicated by Canada Post and we can coordinate the best location for your package to be delivered.</p>
                        <p>If you are unable to retrieve your package from the post office and are concerned your medication might expire, call us and we’ll be happy to assist you. If you are receiving items that need to be refrigerated, like insulin, we will ship them to you in specialized coolers and coordinate delivery with you ahead of time to make sure your medication is not left sitting for more than 2 business days.</p>
                        <p>If you change your shipping address, please update your contact information and address right away from within the E-Pharmacy app or by logging on to our website. You can also call or email our office.</p>
                        <p>E-Pharmacy will contact you if your medication is on manufacturer backorder and work with you to make sure you are still getting the medication you need. We will still ship you any other medications you ordered that are not affected by any such back order.</p>
                        <h3>Safety and Quality</h3>
                        <p>E-Pharmacy advises you to always follow your doctor’s instructions for taking your medication: take the prescribed amount of the medication you should take for the prescribed length of time you should take it. This is the best thing you can do to make sure you get the full benefits from your medication and prevent additional health complications. We understand that some medications may have unpleasant side effects or be difficult to administer, and that is why E-Pharmacy pharmacists are available to offer clinical advice when dealing with these issues.</p>
                        <p>E-Pharmacy is fully accredited and licensed through its provincial College, Association or Society. E-Pharmacy only dispenses medications that have been approved for sale by Health Canada.</p>
